This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and text classification. Additionally, the paper proposes a deep neural network, which is a common technique used in machine learning and falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of attention weights, which is a popular technique in natural language processing and falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well. Finally, the paper discusses the hierarchical composition of phrases and clauses, which is a concept that falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
